deck: Based on a real life San Francisco legend, The King of Pain acts as one of Desire's minions.
description:
The King of Pain is derived from a Victorian era San Francisco man who made a fortune selling lineaments and ointments, before getting into gambling debt and committing suicide. Neil Gaiman included his version in the Sandman The Sandman #31 - Three Septembers and a January where he acts of Desire of the Endless' minions, tempting the Emperor of the United States.

Writer John Ney Reiber used him in the mini-series Mythos: The Final Tour where he acts as the manager for rock star Adam Case, which he wants to bring about the end of the world.
name: King of Pain

deck: King of the Royal Robot family.
name: King Robot

deck: Robot janitor who murders Princess Robot and kidnaps the newborn son of Prince Robot IV.
description:
Origin

A citizen of Robot Kingdom, Dengo had a son named Jokum. One day, Jokum got diarrhea from drinking the water from his village's stream. The doctors said they could do little for commoners without insurance. Jokum died.

Years later, Dengo was working as a janitor at the royal palace. This way, he could get close to Princess Robot and her newborn son. He told her the story about his son, before he killed the Princess. He took the newborn baby.
name: Dengo

deck: American professional wrestler
description:
Dusty Rhodes, "The American Dream," was a retired American professional wrestler. He was the father of Cody and Dustin Runnels, who both are currently under contract with World Wrestling Entertainment. Rhodes. He was also the brother-in-law of wrestlers Nasty Boy Jerry Saggs and Tugboat/Typhoon. Rhodes was inducted into the WWE Hall of Fame in 2007. He appeared earlier in 2015 in WWE programming as his two sons briefly feuded.

He died on June 11, 2015, at the age of 69-years old.
